Here's a simple Arduino code for blinking an LED connected to pin 9:
```cpp
// Define the LED pin
const int ledPin = 9;

void setup() {
  // Initialize the LED pin as an output
  pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);
}

void loop() {
  // Turn the LED on
  digitalWrite(ledPin, HIGH);
  // Wait for 1 second
  delay(1000);
  // Turn the LED off
  digitalWrite(ledPin, LOW);
  // Wait for 1 second
  delay(1000);
}
```
This code uses the `digitalWrite` function to set the LED pin high (on) or low (off) and the `delay` function to pause the program for a specified amount of time.

